  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Hurricane Maria Cash Transfer Programming</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project aims to aid families affected by Hurricane Maria in Puerto Rico to reestablish livelihoods, by issuing cash vouchers to 330 most-affected families in the municipality of Adjuntas and Utuardo. The project is directly implemented by LWR. The cash vouchers will be issued by the Adjuntas Cooperative Bank. LWR staff and consultants will work closely with the cooperative bank to submit lists of beneficiaries that have been identified in the needs assessment process, and the cooperative will issue cash vouchers in the names of those beneficiaries. The vouchers will be distributed by LWR and can be redeemed by beneficiaries when presenting them at the Cooperative Bank along with a valid Identification.</narrative>
  </description>
